          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Two small CH(2) targets, 10*10*2.3-mm**3 and",
                " 10*10*1.5-mm**3, were used for data taking while two",
                "corresponding C-targets, 10*10*1-mm**3 and 10*10*0.5-",
                "mm*3, were used to find the background contribution.",
                "The targets were oriented at an angle of 21-degree",
                "with respect to the beam direction to reduce the energy",
                "loss of the recoil protons."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "TELES",
                "SCIN",
                "SCIN"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Two monitor telescope.",
                "Two scintillators 5*5-cm**2 and 8*8-cm**2",
                "detected P-P elastic scattering events in coincidence."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "MWDC"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Two the multi-wire ionization chambers."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "COMMENT": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "-By authors. Finally the relative cross sections were",
                "obtained by dividing by the solid-angle Monte-Carlo",
                "corrections, the jacobian and the monitor value.",
                "The statistical error on the monitor normalization is",
                "less than 0.3%.",
                "The relative cross section are given normalized",
                "internally with respect to the average 90-degree value.",
                "The errors are due only to the statistics of each",
                "particular angle, without propagation of the error at",
                " 90-degree.",
                "An absolute normalization of the distribution is",
                "available from previous 90-degree studies with the",
                "current apparatus providing purely experimental",
                "results."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ERR-ANALYS": [
